title: Poor app; jazz selection; search engine
text:
The app is poor. Busy UI. Key controls buried. All around ADHD experience, plus IMPOSSIBLE to build playlist by adding albums. Curated suggestions are oddly poor. Jazz selection is so-so and infested with old-time crooners. Great â€œsecond-tierâ€ artists (i.e., not Miles, Coltrane, Monk, and so on) such as Fuller, Mobley, Joe Henderson, Golson, Dolphy, and Bill Evans have poor selections. Poor curation and algorithm for presented choices. Hard to customize. Suggested playlists are current hoo-haa whom I would never listen to.

And, the search engine is astoundingly poor:  E.g., I wanted to listen to the guitar solo by Neil Young on the song â€œCowgirl in the Sandâ€ from the album â€œEverybody Knows This Is Nowhere.â€ After 15 minutes of searching through the search engine, I gave up.
